🟥 0. All Rights Reserved Except Where Explicitly Granted
All rights not expressly granted in this license are reserved by the owner.
If this license does not explicitly allow an action, that action is forbidden.

1. Private Use Only
You may use, modify, and experiment with the code privately.
You may not publicly redistribute modified or unmodified versions of the code.

2. No Public Distribution
You may not:

Publish the code publicly

Upload it to public repositories

Share it publicly in any form

Distribute modified or unmodified versions to the public

If you wish to propose changes, you must do so through a pull request to the original repository.

🟥 2b. No Hosting, No Mirrors, No Public Access
You may not host, mirror, or expose the code in any way that makes it publicly accessible, intentionally or accidentally.
This includes:

Public Git servers

Public file servers

Web hosting

Cloud storage with public links

Private use must remain private.

🟥 2c. No Extractable Distribution
You may not distribute any product, binary, executable, or compiled form that contains the MultiRaptor source code or any form of the code that can be reasonably extracted, decompiled, reverse‑engineered, or recovered.

This includes, but is not limited to:

Embedding MultiRaptor in a public binary

Shipping an executable that contains the interpreter or runtime

Distributing obfuscated or minified versions

Distributing bytecode or intermediate forms

Any distribution where the MultiRaptor code can be reconstructed with reasonable effort

If MultiRaptor is included inside a public project, it must be included only as a private, non‑extractable component, and the MultiRaptor code itself must not be accessible, bundled, or recoverable.

3. No Commercial Use
You may not:

Sell the code

Use the code in a commercial product

Use the code to generate profit

License the code to others

This license grants zero commercial rights.

🟥 3b. Allowed Use Inside Public Projects (Important Clarification)
You may use this code inside a public project (such as a game, OS, engine, or Minecraft clone), as long as:

The MultiRaptor code itself is not redistributed publicly

The MultiRaptor code is not modified and released publicly

The MultiRaptor code keeps its original name and identity

Any modifications remain private

You do not rebrand, rename, or claim ownership of the code

Example allowed use:
✔ Using MultiRaptor internally inside a public game
✔ Using MultiRaptor as a scripting engine inside a public OS
✔ Using MultiRaptor as a private dependency in a public project

Example forbidden use:
✘ Publishing MultiRaptor’s source code
✘ Renaming it to “ScrappyLang” and releasing it
✘ Releasing modified versions
✘ Bundling the source code in a downloadable package

🟥 3d. No Machine Learning or AI Training Use
You may not use the code, in whole or in part, for:

Training machine learning models

Fine‑tuning existing models

Evaluating AI systems

Automated code generation

Dataset creation

Embedding into LLMs or AI pipelines

This restriction applies regardless of whether the model or system is public, private, commercial, or experimental.

Educational Exception
Certified educational institutions (such as schools, universities, or accredited training programs) may use the code for teaching and learning purposes only, provided that:

The code is not published or redistributed

Students do not publicly release modified versions

The code is not used for machine learning, dataset creation, or AI training

All use remains non‑commercial

This exception does not grant any rights to publish, distribute, or commercialize the code.

🟥 5c. No Public Derivative Languages or Systems
You may not create, publish, or distribute any programming language, tool, framework, or system that is derived from, based on, or inspired by MultiRaptor, even if:

The MultiRaptor source code is not directly included

The derivative language is rewritten from scratch

The derivative language uses different syntax or branding

The derivative language is claimed to be “new”

Any derivative language or system must remain private and may not be released publicly under any circumstances.

This prevents:

Rebranding MultiRaptor into a new language

Creating a “ScrappyLang” or similar fork

Publishing a modified or rewritten version

Using MultiRaptor as the foundation for a public tool or engine

All derivative works remain private and under this license.

